15 WHEREAS, timely access to disability benefits is essential for individuals with lupus to
16 afford medical care, medications, and basic living expenses necessary for their survival and
17 well-being.
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
19 this body urges Congress to prioritize reforms to the federal disability determination process
20 to address the unique challenges faced by individuals living with lupus, including, but not
21 limited to:
22 (a) Expedited processing for claims involving lupus;
23 (b) Improved education and training for disability claims examiners and adjudicators on
24 lupus' medical complexities;
25 (c) Development of clearer guidelines for evaluating lupus-related disability claims to
26 reduce inconsistencies and high denial rates; and
27 (d) Increased funding for the Social Security Administration to improve claim processing
28 times and resources for individuals with lupus.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that Congress is urged to collaborate with medical experts,
30 patient advocacy organizations, and community stakeholders to ensure that lupus patients
31 receive fair and timely access to the disability benefits they deserve.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 President of the United States Senate, to the Speaker of the United States House of
35 Representatives, and to each member of the Congressional delegation from this state.
